    <text id="B0199T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>This communication from Jordan to Waldo concerns two claims. Jordan writes that
                    one is in order, but he needs clarification on the second one. The substance of
                    the matter is unclear from the letter. </p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office Fifth Division,
                    Seventh Sub-District of Virginia,<lb/>Counties of Bath, Alleghany and
                    Rockbridge.
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-11-06"><abbr expan="November">Nov</abbr> 6 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Lexington, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Mr Waldo</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your line <abbr expan="received">recd</abbr> relating to the <abbr
                        expan="Railroad">RR</abbr> claim &amp; Transportation matter. The first
                    is collected and all right the other I cannot understand and can get no
                    information concerning it but will send the money back and take the
                        <unclear>risk</unclear>.</p>

                <p>As soon as I get my <unclear>assets</unclear> in which I am expecting daily will
                    send you amount covering back that is $27.14/00 dollars.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="John">Jno</abbr> W Jordan</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
